                            <comment id="277372" author="mhanafi" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2020 20:28:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please close&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="273093" author="ashehata" created="Wed, 17 Jun 2020 14:02:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes it should be able to. A config like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Client:
lnetctl route add --net o2ib3 --gateway hop1@o2ib1

HOP 1:
lnetctl route add --net o2ib3 --gateway hop2@o2ib2

HOP 2:
lnetctl route add --net o2ib1 --gateway hop1@o2ib2

Server:
lnetctl route add --net o2ib1 --gateway hop2@o2ib3&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="273073" author="adilger" created="Wed, 17 Jun 2020 10:25:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mahmoud, I believe that the multi-hop routing is possible, and is in use in some sites.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Amir, could you please confirm.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
